Gaby Moreno @gaby_moreno x Oscar Isaac “Luna de Xelaju”
.
It’s not every day you get to collaborate with some of your close friends on the same project. This was one of those rare opportunities and came together after Diego and Gaby had reached out about collaborating with Oscar on a music project.
. 
Inspired by the simplicity of the space, and the eerie melody of the song- we utilized a mix of Mole beams and soft top light to provide the freedom for Steadicam operator Colin Macdonnell to move about the space and craft a dynamic “oner”. 
.
Oscar and Gaby were an absolute joy to work with and were truly electric together on camera. I was particularly taken aback by their vocals and how well they complimented each other. 
. 
Shout out to our incredible crew for making this one happen, and to colorist Mikey Rossiter for pushing it across the finish line with such a lovely grade. 
.

Toyota- “Upgrade”
.
Had a blast shooting this spot for the new Corolla with director @grajper and some wonderful folks in both Warsaw and Barcelona. The challenge was to integrate lifestyle footage into running footage of the vehicle via some intricate transitions. Truly took an army to pull this one off and we couldn’t have done it without all of y’all!

Shot on Sony Venice + Olympus OM primes!

The Nile river at sunrise, somewhere in northern Uganda circa 2018. My mate Jeff and I were waiting on this ferry to take us to the other side. While we waited, a band comprised of a couple elders played to my right. To this day I can still remember the melody of what they were playing. The sky was showing off with the most spectator light in this moment and I love how the Xpan format captured this composition. I love rediscovering old negatives.

Boost infinite: Apple iPhone 15 pro “Garden”
•
Had a blast shooting this spot for the iphone 15 Pro with some new friends over at @the.mayda.creative.co . We wanted to create a dynamic world of heightened surrealism that would only exist in one’s imagination. I told my team I wanted this to feel like a flowing oil painting with subtle movement in the lighting, wind, and motivated camera moves. Thanks you Ben and Carl for bringing me on this fantastic adventure, and much love to our crew of legends that pushed these spots across the finish line!

Apple iPhone 15 pro x Boost Infinite: “Explorer”
•
From the fine folks at @the.mayda.creative.co and directors Ben Smith and Carl Addy. We wanted to create a dynamic world of heightened surrealism that would only exist in one’s imagination- a moving oil painting if you will. In this particular spot our team motivated a cloudy misty marine layer that parted to reveal the last few moments of a colorful sunset you’d see in a place like the Grand Canyon. Utilizing a mix of hard, soft and colored light we melded LED tech with more traditional tungsten fixtures to create the look. Much love to our crew of legends that pushed these spots across the finish line!
•
